data.reasoningText:
For the LongRunningOperation files, the pattern is:```csharp
var lroDetails = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default).ToObjectFromJson<Dictionary<string, string>>();
```

`ToObjectFromJson<T>()` is an extension method on `BinaryData` that calls `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T>()`. To make it AOT-compatible, I can replace:```csharp
var lroData = ModelReaderWriter.Write(rehydrationToken, ModelReaderWriterOptions.Json, AzureResourceManagerContext.Default);


var lroDetails = JsonSerializer.Deserialize(lroData, ArmSerializationContext.Default.DictionaryStringString);
```

I need to add the System.Text.Json using statement and update all 4 files with this approach.

