public override void Write(Utf8JsonWriter writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType model, JsonSerializerOptions options)
{
    writer.WritePropertyName("type");
    writer.WriteStringValue(model.ToString());
}
```

So `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, ManagedServiceIdentityType, jOptions)` writes:
- `"type"` property name
- The string value of the type

I can inline this as:
```csharp
writer.WritePropertyName("type"u8);


writer.WriteStringValue(ManagedServiceIdentityType.ToString());
```

